\begin_inset Formula $p/q$
\end_inset

, of 
\begin_inset Formula $OP$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The length 
\begin_inset Formula $OL$
\end_inset

 cannot have a rational measure.
 For, if possible, let 
\begin_inset Formula $m/n$
\end_inset

 be the measure of 
\begin_inset Formula $OL$
\end_inset

.
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\therefore\qquad\frac{p}{q}\sqrt{2}=\frac{m}{n}\mbox{ or }\sqrt{2}=\frac{mq}{np},
\]

\end_inset

which states that 
\begin_inset Formula $\sqrt{2}$
\end_inset

